  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmers Inputs Loans and Member Services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IFCU (1993) LTD (Iringa Farmers&#x2019; Cooperative Union) is a secondary level cooperative society registered in 28th May 1993 with registration No. 5051. The union was previously known as IMCU LTD which stood for Iringa Mufindi Cooperative Union  this was established in 1985. IFCU LTD operates in four District councils of Iringa  Kilolo  Mufindi and Mafinga town council. The Union started with 32-member primary societies and is currently having 37-member primary societies. In order to become a member  one has to pay TZS 250 000 entrance fees and buy 50 shares valued at TZS 10 000 each (500 000TZS) within two years&#x2019; time. According to the Cooperative societies Act Number 6 of 2013 it is prohibited a member to buy more than 20% of the total union shares. The primary objective of the union is to promote economic development of the member primary societies through agricultural production and joint marketing of their produce. The common needs of establishing this union were inputs and marketing related issues  mainly how members could access farm inputs and reliable market at reasonable time and price. 
  
The management of the union is led by the board which comprises chairperson  Vice chairperson  four members and secretary cum manager who enter into the board meetings for his or her position. The Member&#x2019;s General Meeting is the highest decision &#x2013; making organ of the union normally there are three types of meetings depending on the nature of issues to be discussed. The annual and ordinary meetings where annual estimates and elections issues are being discussed. Further  there are special meetings in case of emergencies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IFCU LTD goal is to improve  services provision to members   by providing farmers inputs loans to members (AMCOS)  establishment of Farm Clinic Mechanization Program  Market link between Union  buyer ( Silver Land Co. LTD)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2019  according to the IFCU LTD action plan  the collaboration will start with  strengthening of the organization through financial management and governance training  entrepreneurship training  Good Practice in Agricultural production  exchange visit mission to maize marketing union</narrative>
  </description>
